---
import SiteLayout from '../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';

export const meta = {
  title: 'Inside the Alleged Russian Operation to Trigger Anti-Government Protests in Angola',
  description: 'Two Russians and two Angolans are facing trial in Luanda over allegations of terrorism, espionage, and attempting to foment anti-government protests linked to a post-Wagner Group network.',
  category: 'world',
  published: '2026-03-24',
};

const schema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "NewsArticle",
  "headline": meta.title,
  "description": meta.description,
  "datePublished": meta.published,
  "dateModified": meta.published,
  "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Trunk Press" },
  "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Trunk Press" },
  "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://trunkpress.photonbuilder.com/inside-the-alleged-russian-operation-to-trigger-anti" }
};
---

<SiteLayout site="trunkpress" title={meta.title} description={meta.description} canonical="https://trunkpress.photonbuilder.com/inside-the-alleged-russian-operation-to-trigger-anti" schema={schema}>
  <article class="tp-article max-w-3xl mx-auto px-5 py-12">
    <!-- Category + Date -->
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
      <span class="text-xs font-black tracking-[2px] uppercase text-[var(--accent-color)]">🌍 WORLD</span>
      <span class="text-xs text-[var(--text-secondary)]">March 24, 2026</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Headline -->
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black leading-tight mb-4 text-[var(--text-primary)]">
      Inside the Alleged Russian Operation to Trigger Anti-Government Protests in Angola
    </h1>

    <!-- Lede -->
    <p class="text-lg font-bold text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-8 border-l-4 border-[var(--accent-color)] pl-4">
      A trial in Luanda is pulling back the curtain on a suspected covert Russian influence operation in Angola. Two Russian nationals and two Angolans face charges including terrorism and espionage for allegedly attempting to overthrow the current regime and interfere in the country's upcoming presidential election.
    </p>

    <!-- Article body -->
    <div class="space-y-5 text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-3">What Happened</h2>
      <p>
        On March 24, 2026, four men — two Russian nationals and two Angolans — began their trial in Luanda. The Russian defendants, identified as political consultant Igor Ratchin, 38, and veteran translator Lev Lakshtanov, 64, were arrested in August 2024. They are accused alongside Angolan journalist Amor Carlos Tomé, 38, and UNITA political leader Francisco Oliveira, 32.
      </p>
      <p>
        According to the Angolan public prosecutor's office, the group faces 11 charges, including criminal association, terrorism, espionage, and influence peddling. Investigators allege the operation's goal was to foment violent protests to provoke political change — either by bringing the opposition UNITA party to power or forcing internal shifts within the ruling MPLA party leadership ahead of the next presidential election.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-3">Why It Matters</h2>
      <p>
        The indictment details a sophisticated attempt at foreign interference in an African democracy. Prosecutors claim the initial team of Russian operatives arrived in Luanda in 2024 under the pretext of opening a Russian cultural center — a project that was never realized. Instead, authorities say the operatives hired local figures, including Tomé and Oliveira, to execute a disinformation campaign and stir up anti-government sentiment.
      </p>
      <p>
        The defendants have consistently denied the accusations, maintaining their innocence. However, their prolonged detention and the severe charges highlight the Angolan government's serious approach to perceived threats against national security and sovereignty.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-3">The Bigger Picture</h2>
      <p>
        The Angola trial is drawing international attention due to the defendants' alleged ties to Russian paramilitary networks. Investigations have linked the operation to the "African Political Scientists" project, also known as Africa Politology. This shadow network is described by prosecutors as a post-Yevgeny Prigozhin offshoot of the defunct Wagner Group, operating under an umbrella structure called Africa Org.
      </p>
      <p>
        Following Prigozhin's death in August 2023, Russian operatives appear to be using new tactics to maintain and expand Moscow's influence across the continent. Observers note that while the Wagner Group was known for deploying mercenaries to conflict zones, this new iteration seems focused on subtler methods of destabilization, such as election interference and exploiting local political grievances.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mt-8 mb-3">What's Next</h2>
      <p>
        As the trial unfolds, it is expected to reveal more details about the depth of Russian infiltration into Angolan civil society. Six other individuals linked to the operation reportedly managed to leave the country before authorities could apprehend them, leaving Ratchin, Lakshtanov, Tomé, and Oliveira to face the justice system.
      </p>
      <p>
        The outcome of this high-profile case will not only determine the fate of the accused but could also set a precedent for how African nations confront covert foreign influence campaigns on the continent.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Tags -->
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 mt-10 pt-6 border-t border-[var(--border-color)]">
      <span class="text-xs bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded px-3 py-1 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">#Angola</span>
      <span class="text-xs bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded px-3 py-1 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">#Russia</span>
      <span class="text-xs bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded px-3 py-1 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">#WagnerGroup</span>
      <span class="text-xs bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded px-3 py-1 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">#Geopolitics</span>
      <span class="text-xs bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded px-3 py-1 text-[var(--text-secondary)]">#AfricaPolitology</span>
    </div>

    <!-- Related -->
    <div class="mt-8 p-5 bg-[var(--card-bg)] border border-[var(--border-color)] rounded">
      <h3 class="text-sm font-black tracking-wider text-[var(--accent-color)] mb-2">RELATED STORIES</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)]">More coverage coming. This is a developing story.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</SiteLayout>
